  "texts": [
    "Importantly, LLMs have also emerged as subjects of inquiry, particularly regarding how humans interact with them.",
    "Early studies examine human-LLM dynamics in domains such as community-based content moderation (Mohammadi & Yasseri, 2025), countering misinformation (Rani et al., 2025), reducing belief in conspiracy theories (Costello et al., 2024), improving online political discourse (Argyle et al., 2023), and alleviating political polarization (Walter, 2025).",
    "Experimental designs for studying human-LLM interactions can be placed on a spectrum of sophistication.",
    "At the most basic level, participants are directed to an external public platform to interact with the model before returning to the study.",
    "While easy to implement, this approach offers limited control over the interaction process."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Early studies examine human-LLM dynamics in domains such as community-based content moderation (Mohammadi & Yasseri, 2025), countering misinformation (Rani et al., 2025), reducing belief in conspiracy theories (Costello et al., 2024), improving online political discourse (Argyle et al., 2023), and alleviating political polarization (Walter, 2025)."
